yself growing more and more frustrated with the situation. I've tried various solutions, like asking friends to watch him for a while, contacting the [Organization] for a hospital room, and even considering hospice care for additional support.. I can empathize with the immense frustration and exhaustion you've been experiencing. The lack of sleep and the constant demands of caregiving can take a significant toll on both your physical and emotional wellbeing. It's important to remember that your feelings are valid, and it's natural to feel angry and overwhelmed in this situation.\\n\\nOne approach we could explore is the use of cognitive-behavioral techniques to help manage your emotions and responses to your husband's restlessness. We could work on identifying and challenging negative thoughts and beliefs, as well as practicing relaxation and stress management techniques to help you cope with the situation more effectively.\\n\\nAdditionally, it may be helpful to explore alternative solutions that address the root cause of the problem, such as working with your husband's healthcare team to find a more effective medication regimen or exploring non-pharmacological interventions, like sleep hygiene practices or relaxation techniques.\\n\\nUltimately, it's essential to remember that self-care and prioritizing your own needs are crucial components of effective caregiving. By taking care of yourself, you'll be better equipped to handle the demands of caregiving and maintain a healthier, more balanced life. I've been feeling increasingly anxious and agitated lately, especially when it comes to my husband, [Name]. His restlessness at night has been keeping me awake, and I've found myself growing more and more frustrated with the situation. I've tried various solutions, like asking friends to watch him for a while, contacting the [Organization] for a hospital room, and even considering hospice care for additional support.. I'm here to offer a safe and supportive space for yo